06/04/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Some 1,600 passengers and crew were evacuated from a Greek cruise ship that struck rocks near the Island of Santorini on Thursday (April 5th). 
Most of the 1,200 passengers were American, along with more than 100 Spaniards and two school groups from Canada aboard the Sea Diamond. 
A dozen ships, six navy helicopters, two military transport planes and four naval vessels were dispatched to the scene. 
According to unconfirmed reports, a French family may be missing after the incident. 
(Naftemporiki - 06/04/07; AP, DPA, ERT, ANA-MPA - 05/04/07)
